reviewText:
Gems, Mercury, Sulfur and Crystals are replaced with Blood Crystals;
Heroes are caped at level 30;
No random map generator;
If you play offline you only have 2 heroes per town to chose from;
Creatures are put in 3 tiers (3 core, 3 elite and 1 champion); Creatures in same tier are almost the same;
No Mage Guild;
No Academy or Rampart (Sylvan) factions;
Shades of Darkness campaign is unplayable (Black Screen bug in first mission);
Dynasty system gives you unfair advantage vs AI (It also doesn't work in offline mode);
All factions have very similar creatures (Creatures that attack and return like harpies for example);
User Interface is poor;
Hero progression and acquiring spells is less random.

4/10

Just buy Heroes of Might & Magic III: Complete on GOG or Heroes of Might & Magic V: Tribes of the East.

IMHO One of the Best strategy games ever, along with HoMM3. Beautiful graphic, and a lot of new features. For more exact information feel free to read this: http://heroescommunity.com/viewthread.php3?TID=33655

If you played Heroes III, I am sure you will love this one too.
//Try to get it on -75% sale, or buy on outpost[www.tf2outpost.com]

PROs :
- Is HEROES;
- Gold : Danse Macabre Adventure, Pirates of the Savage Sea, Shades of Darkness;
- Over 10 campaigns;
- Hero: Anastasia, Faction: Stronghold; :D
- Was better than IV and V;
- Good spell effects.

CONs :
- That fu*king black screen before every battle or building entrance. After almost 5 years there is no FIX. Damn! :steamfacepalm:
